snippet.textDisplay:
At 0:55 I just learned a small detail that some people exist in because of potential danger. As a black man I’ve never had to think “ better not listen to my music as I walk, I need to pay attention to my surroundings”

I can see how women think about those things especially if their walking at night, but do any guys go through these thoughts?

I’ve had moments where it’s dark at night, I’m wearing a trench coat hood up, I’m 6’2. The person walking towards me will cross the street and then cross back after passing me...and I think to myself “ I don’t blame you, better safe than sorry”
I know I’m not a threat to them and have no intentions of harming them, but I’m aware of my physical appearance. Such a funny world we live in.
